 * ğŸ”¹ Case 1: Jab Frontend + Backend + API sab kuchh tumhare hi control me ho
 *
 * - Tum hi frontend bana rahe ho (website / app)
 * - Tum hi backend bana rahe ho
 * - Tum hi API use kar rahe ho
 * - User sirf page refresh ya app reopen karta hai
 *
 * ğŸ‘‰ Is case me:
 * - Agar tum backend ya API me koi logic change kar do
 * - Ya response structure / validation rules update kar do
 *
 * âœ”ï¸ To jaise hi frontend reload hota hai, sab changes automatically reflect ho jate hain
 * âœ”ï¸ Kyunki frontend aur backend dono tumhare control me hain
 *
 * âŒ Is situation me API versioning (v1, v2, etc.) dena mandatory nahi hota
 *
 * ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 *
 * ğŸ”¹ Case 2: Jab koi aur tumhari API use kar raha ho
 *
 * - Tum API bana rahe ho
 * - Koi third-party developer tumhari API use kar raha hai
 *   (uski website / Android app / iOS app)
 * - Uske frontend ka control tumhare paas nahi hota
 *
 * ğŸ‘‰ Is case me agar tum:
 * - API ka response structure change kar do
 * - Field ka naam change kar do
 * - Validation ya logic change kar do
 *
 * âŒ To uska existing app / website toot sakta hai
 * âŒ Kyunki uska frontend automatically update nahi hota
 *
 * âœ”ï¸ Isi problem ko solve karne ke liye API versioning use ki jati hai
 *
 * ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 *
 * ğŸ”¹ API Versioning ka matlab (v1, v2, etc.)
 *
 * - v1 = purana stable version (existing users ke liye)
 * - v2 = naya improved version (new features / changes ke saath)
 *
 * Example:
 *   /api/v1/users  â†’ purane users ke liye safe
 *   /api/v2/users  â†’ naye changes ke saath
 *
 * âœ”ï¸ Isse purane users ka app nahi toot-ta
 * âœ”ï¸ Aur naye users ko updated API mil jati hai
 *
 * ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 *
 *   Final Conclusion:
 *
 * - Agar API sirf tumhari hi website/app ke liye hai
 *   â†’ Versioning optional hai
 *
 * - Agar API ko koi aur apne project me use kar raha hai
 *   â†’ Versioning compulsory hai
 *
    âœ”ï¸ Private API (own frontend)
      â†’ Versioning not compulsory

   âœ”ï¸ Public / Shared API
      â†’ Versioning compulsory

  âœ”ï¸ Enterprise / Mobile apps / Third-party
      â†’ Versioning MUST

